US border "Super-tunnel" discovered for the drug smuggling
At the border between Mexico and the USA observers discovered and deactivated a "super-tunnel" for the drug smuggling.
As the US customs authorities informed, the more than 500 meters long tube was endowed with electricity, railway tracks and a ventilating system between Tijuana and San Diego.
Three suspects were arrested accordingly, confiscated eight tons of marihuana as well as almost 150 kilograms of cocaine.
The tunnel had not been taken according to the information in use yet.
"These cartels are stupid if they think they could "durchgraben" under the radar" the general state attorney of the US district Southern California, Laura Duffy said, at a press conference in front of a warehouse in San Diego, where the one end of the tunnel had been discovered.
Turned onto the drug gangs Duffy insured: "If your wide builds such tunnels and attempts to use it, we are decided to turn that into a gigantic waste of your dirty money".
Both the US authorities and the Mexican security forces are in a continuous-fight against the drug cartels.
Since became 2006 in Mexico more than killed to 77th 000 people in connection with the drug criminality.
Constructed by experts
Because of the extensive equipment of the tunnel the observers assume that it was constructed by architects and engineers and that the construction used about a year.
The railway construction siding track was so equipped, that there electrical practiced cars could be used.
On Mexican page the access lies in a building which is 80 meters of the border away.
According to authorities a ladder leads 20 meters into the depth to the actual tunnel entry
The tunnel has a cross-section view of 1.20 meters height and 90 centimeters of width.
It would have been also suitable with in order to support the illegal immigration direction of USA.
Two of the suspects were arrested in connection with the cocaine-find.
The third parties party, a Mexican, were grabbed because of the confiscated marihuana.
